    "description": "~Story~<br />\r\n-The Spiriting Away-<br />\r\nAn incident visited Gensokyo alongside summer.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOne by one, things all over Gensokyo began to disappear.<br />\r\nIt started with living things such as fairies and humans,<br />\r\nthen continued on to affect even inanimate objects like buildings.<br />\r\nThese mysterious happenings have struck fear into the people of Gensokyo.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIs this an incident...?<br />\r\nJust now, four individuals have set out amidst these strange events.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSelect one of these four protagonists,<br />\r\nand resolve the spiriting away incident plaguing all of Gensokyo!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThere are over 100 allies called &quot;shikigami&quot; to recruit.<br />\r\nCombine shikigami however you like and bring the incident to its resolution!<br />\r\n<br />\r\n~Game Systems~<br />\r\n&quot;Touhou Gensou Maroku W ~ The Devil of Decline&quot; is a 2D turn-based RPG.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter the prologue, you'll be able to select one of four protagonists.<br />\r\nThere are no major changes to enemy strength or the story between them,<br />\r\nbut there are differences in their ease of play, your initial party members,<br />\r\nthe type and number Spell Cards you start with, and so on.<br />\r\n(The characters you didn't choose will join your party later.)<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDevil of Decline's main selling point is its shikigami system.<br />\r\nPutting it simply, it's a system that lets you &quot;equip your allies.&quot;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n*Touhou Gensou Maroku W is a Touhou Project fangame.<br />\r\nTouhou Project is a copyright of Team Shanghai Alice.",
